---
description: Prevent hallucinated APIs, silent failures, and over-refactoring
alwaysApply: true
---

# Anti-hallucination

- NEVER invent npm packages, env vars, or API routes — verify in `package.json`, `.env.example`, or `server/sub.md`
- NEVER assume files exist; read or search before importing
- NEVER empty `catch` blocks; log or rethrow with context
- NEVER rewrite unrelated files in the same task
- If unsure about a signature, open the defining file first

When the user says a path or command failed, diagnose from terminal output — do not guess fixes.
